&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot; data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MessageBody&quot;&gt;TeccWeb, a member of the Alan Allman Associates Ecosystem, is one of North America&#39;s largest providers of Epicor ERP services, founded in 2014.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;TeccWeb is an Epicor Service Partner specializing in the implementation and optimization of Epicor ERP solutions for mid-market companies worldwide. Our team consists of certified Epicor consultants with expertise in information technology, database development, program customization, SSRS, Crystal Reports, business process re-engineering, and employee training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;With our diverse skill set and collaborative approach, we help clients solve complex business challenges and maximize the value of their ERP systems. Our success is built on strong, long-term partnerships with our clients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;We are seeking an experienced&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Epicor Kinetic Financial Implementation Specialist&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;to lead the configuration, deployment, and optimization of our Epicor Kinetic (ERP) financial modules, with a critical focus on the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Cost Accounting&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;and Avalara tax integration (Epicor Tax Connect)&lt;/strong&gt;. The ideal candidate will possess a deep understanding of manufacturing cost structures, corporate accounting knowledge, US/international tax compliance, and hands-on experience in&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;implementing&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Epicor for manufacturing companies&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;and integrating&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Avalara solutions (e.g., AvaTax, Exemption Certificate Management)&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;within an ERP system. This role is crucial for ensuring accurate financial reporting, robust internal controls, and seamless global tax compliance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role and Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;As a Senior Epicor ERP Implementation Consultant, you will play a key role in ensuring the success of our clients’ projects. Your responsibilities will include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul type=&quot;disc&quot;&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Epicor Kinetic Implementation: Lead or actively participate in all phases of the Epicor Kinetic Financial Management implementation lifecycle, including requirements gathering, system design, configuration, testing, training, and post-go-live support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Avalara Integration &amp;amp; Tax Compliance:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul type=&quot;circle&quot;&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Serve as the Subject Matter Expert (SME) for the Avalara module integration within Epicor Kinetic (Epicor Tax Connect).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Configure and test complex tax scenarios, including Sales &amp;amp; Use Tax, VAT, GST, and related compliance rules within Avalara/Epicor.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Ensure accurate tax code mapping, address validation, and nexus tracking.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Manage the setup and process for Exemption Certificate Management (ECM) to maintain audit readiness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Collaborate with the finance team to automate tax reporting and filing processes (e.g., Avalara Returns).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Financial Module Expertise: Configure and manage core financial modules, including:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul type=&quot;circle&quot;&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;General Ledger (GL) and Chart of Accounts design/mapping.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;Accounts Payable (AP) and Accounts Receivable (AR).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;x_MsoNorma

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;TeccWeb is an Epicor Service Partner specializing in the implementation and optimization of Epicor ERP solutions for mid-market companies worldwide. Our team consists of certified Epicor consultants with expertise in information technology, database development, program customization, SSRS, Crystal Reports, business process re-engineering, and employee training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With our diverse skill set and collaborative approach, we help clients solve complex business challenges and maximize the value of their ERP systems. Our success is built on strong, long-term partnerships with our clients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking experienced ERP consultants to join our growing team and support our increasing customer base.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role and Responsabilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Senior Epicor ERP Implementation Consultant, you will play a key role in ensuring the success of our clients’ projects. Your responsibilities will include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyzing clients’ business needs and objectives to recommend tailored ERP solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configuring, testing, and deploying the Epicor ERP system based on client requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing user training and change management support to facilitate adoption.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drafting functional specifications for custom enhancements, integrations, and reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing and tracking project progress, including resource planning, prioritization, and deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshooting and providing technical and functional support to clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assisting with data migration and integration with existing systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborating closely with internal teams and clients to ensure seamless implementations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintaining Epicor certification and continuously developing your skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Business Administration, Accounting, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience in Epicor ERP implementation or working within an Epicor ERP environment as a SME/super user.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of Epicor Kinetic: 2 years or more.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous knowledge of Epicor 10 is considered an asset.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Epicor certification is considered an asset.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication and client relationship management skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently while collaborating effectively within a team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Availability for regular travel to client sites in addition to remote work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Offer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fully remote position in Canada or USA (no relocation required).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive salary, based on experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive benefits package, including health, dental, disability, and life insurance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunities for career growth and ongoing training.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Join TeccWeb and be part of a team of experts working on exciting projects!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;TeccWeb is an Epicor Service Partner comprised of a team of experts in Epicor ERP, Information Technology, Database Development, Program Customization, SSRS, Crystal Reports, Business Re-engineering and Employee Training providing enterprise resource planning (ERP) solutions to mid-market companies around the world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our experts come from a wide range of business backgrounds and are certified Epicor consultants. We offer a diverse skill set which enables us to provide our customers with the expertise needed to solve complex business issues successfully. Our success is derived from building strong, long term customer partnerships..&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;YOUR ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a TeccWeb Epicor Tools Developer, you are responsible for customizing, enhancing, and maintaining the Epicor Kinetic ERP system using native Epicor development tools. This role requires a strong blend of technical expertise, business process understanding, and problem-solving skills to meet specific organizational needs and optimize ERP functionality without altering core system code.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY RESPONSABILITIES AND COMPETENCIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Epicor Customization and Development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Epicor Application Studio: Design and implement User Interface (UI) customizations for Kinetic web screens (adding/hiding fields, modifying controls, creating custom forms).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Business Process Management (BPM): Develop and maintain server-side business logic using BPM Directives (Pre/Base/Post Processing) to enforce business rules and automate workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in utilizing C# code within BPMs for complex logic is required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Epicor Functions: Create and manage reusable, encapsulated business logic components using Epicor Functions (written in C#) for specific, complex operations and integrations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data Structure: Design and implement User Defined Tables (UDT) and fields to extend the Epicor data model as required by business needs.&lt;br&gt;Reporting, Data, and Integration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Business Activity Queries (BAQ): Create, optimize, and maintain complex BAQs (including sub-queries and calculated fields) to support custom dashboards, reports, and integrations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dashboards (EDD): Develop and customize Dashboards using BAQs and the Epicor Data Discovery (EDD) platform to provide users with actionable real-time data insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reporting: Design, develop, and modify financial and operational reports, often using SSRS (SQL Server Reporting Services) or other Epicor-supported reporting tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integration: Utilize Epicor&#39;s REST API and Service Connect (if applicable) to facilitate seamless data exchange and integration with external systems, ensuring all transactions respect Epicor&#39;s business objects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;TECHNICAL SILLS AND BEST PRACTICES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Programming Languages: Strong proficiency in C# and familiarity with the .NET framework.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Database: Solid working knowledge of SQL (T-SQL) for data querying and performance optimization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshooting: Ability to use Epicor and browser debugging tools (e.g., Application Studio debug console, F12 developer tools, tracing) to diagnose, troubleshoot, and resolve issues in customizations and BPMs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Best Practices: Adhere to best practices for Epicor development, including maintaining a clear separation between client-side (UI) and server-side (BPM) logic, and using Epicor services over direct database manipulation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
